Re: MP3 player(the physical kind) supporting Unicode or UTF-
by Hyperworm » Tue 09.06.2011 2:36 pm micahcowan wrote:I suspect just about any of Apple's MP3-playing products may support Japanese charactersI'm pretty sure this is the case as well. My iPod touch supports Japanese, as did my 3rd-generation classic iPod years ago.Entry of Japanese characters for searching is also possible on iPod touch.I didn't really want to give this answer because I don't want to make it seem like iPod is the best or only option - I'd prefer to present a balanced general perspective rather than directing you straight to Apple - but unfortunately iPod is the only mp3 player I'm familiar with. ._.Incidentally, it's UTF-16, not 18.
